## Files

- lib/repository/jsonl.ml

## Description

Replace the near-identical _todo_to_json/_note_to_json with a shared helper:

    let _entity_to_json ~entity_type ~id ~title ~content ~status ~created_at ~updated_at =
      `Assoc [
        ("type", `String entity_type);
        ("id", `String (Data.Uuid.Typeid.to_string id));
        ("title", `String (Data.Title.to_string title));
        ("content", `String (Data.Content.to_string content));
        ("status", `String status);
        ("created_at", `String (Data.Timestamp.to_iso8601 created_at));
        ("updated_at", `String (Data.Timestamp.to_iso8601 updated_at));
      ]

Callers: _todo_to_json becomes `_entity_to_json ~entity_type:"todo" ~id:(Todo.id t) ...`

Similarly, unify _parse_todo_record and _parse_note_record into a shared _parse_entity_fields helper that extracts id, title, content, created_at, updated_at, and returns them. The caller supplies the status parser and record constructor.

The entity_record type (Todo/Note variants) stays as-is — the duplication is in the serialization/parsing logic, not the type.

## TDD note

No behavioral change. Existing sync_service tests and JSONL round-trip tests validate correctness. Run dune runtest.
